<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n57075e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n57" href="#n57075e">N57 (VI.B.47)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n57all.htm#n57075e"> 75(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hero leaves</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Im Kampf mit immer anderen Ungeheuern, die kein Mensch bezwingen kann, w&auml;chst Herakles sein &uuml;bermenschliches Wesen aus, aber die letzte Entfaltung seiner g&ouml;ttlichen Natur entf&uuml;hrt den Heros himmelan in Flammen, sie entr&uuml;ckt ihn dem verehrenden Blick im Augenblicke, wo dieser wissend genug w&auml;re, das Wesen des Gottshohnes recht an ihm zu schauen. <br><font color="green">[In the struggle with ever-varied monsters that no human can overcome, Hercules outgrows his superhuman essence; but the last unfolding of his divine nature <mark>carries the hero off</mark> heavenwards in flames; it transports him to a look of reverence at the moment when this look would be knowing enough to see directly into the essence of divine mockery.]</font> <small> Heinrich Zimmer, <a name="HZMI2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HZMI2"><cite title="source">Maya der indische Mythos</cite></a> (1936) 25</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
